    <p>The lease deposit — the rent advance you pay upfront before getting possession of the space — is typically the largest single outflow in a restaurant setup. In Indian cities, this ranges from 3 months to 12 months of rent paid upfront, and it's non-negotiable with most landlords in prime locations.</p>
